---
title: "The Process — Slade Networks"
description: "See exactly how a Slade Networks project works — from free on-site consultation to professional installation and ongoing support in the Finger Lakes, NY."
navActive: process
---
{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block pageStyles %}
  <style>
    .ctaSection { padding: 0 0 72px }

    @media(max-width:700px) {
      .benefitList { grid-template-columns: 1fr }
    }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="heroBadge">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 11 12 14 22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/></svg>
          Clear from start to finish
        </div>
        <h1>How Every Project Works</h1>
        <p class="subtext">
          No surprises, no guesswork. Here's exactly what to expect — from the first conversation to a working system you can rely on.
        </p>

        <div class="steps reveal-stagger" aria-label="Project steps">
          <article class="step">
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">1</div>
              <h2>Free on-site consultation</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              We come to you. We walk through the space, talk through what's not working or what you'd like to add — better Wi-Fi, cameras, phones, or all three — and map the layout so coverage is planned before anything is installed. No phone-call estimates. No guessing from a floor plan.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step">
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">2</div>
              <h2>Custom plan and written quote</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              You'll receive a detailed plan showing where everything goes, what hardware is needed, and exactly what it costs — all in writing before any work begins. No vague estimates, no surprise line items at the end.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step">
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">3</div>
              <h2>Professional installation</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              Equipment goes in cleanly — cables routed neatly, gear mounted properly, everything labeled for easy future service. The result is a finished system that looks and works like a professional job, not a pile of gear crammed in a closet.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step">
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">4</div>
              <h2>Testing and handoff</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              Before we leave, everything is verified — Wi-Fi coverage spot-checked, cameras confirmed recording and accessible remotely, calling tested end-to-end. You get a full walkthrough and your own admin access. Nothing is locked away or hidden behind our login.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step featured">
            <div class="stepBadge">Recommended add-on</div>
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">5</div>
              <h2>Ongoing Support Plan</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              Most post-install issues don't need a site visit — they need someone who knows the system and can fix things remotely, fast. With a support plan, we monitor your network, handle firmware updates proactively, and troubleshoot problems before they disrupt your day.
            </p>
            <p>
              It's the difference between managing a system yourself and having someone watch over it for you. Especially valuable for businesses where downtime has a real cost.
            </p>
            <ul class="benefitList" aria-label="Support plan benefits">
              <li>Remote monitoring</li>
              <li>Priority response times</li>
              <li>Proactive firmware updates</li>
              <li>Remote troubleshooting</li>
              <li>Most issues fixed without a site visit</li>
              <li>One point of contact for anything network</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ctaSection reveal">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ctaInner">
          <div>
            <h2>Step one is easy</h2>
            <p>Tell us what you're dealing with. We'll schedule a free on-site visit and put together a plan that fits.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Schedule your consultation</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
{% endblock %}
